    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-03T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-03T02:00:00-05:00" n="338"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d338">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9172: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-03T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 3, 1937—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 4—6:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>361. 1. According to information reliably reported to have emanated from the
                    highest sources, while Chinese troop movements northward and other military
                    preparations will continue, Chinese plans contemplate no extensive fighting
                    until after an emergency meeting of the National Defence Council August 10 and
                    that after that date a state of (undeclared) war will exist and all the
                    Government’s resources including the air service will be called into action to
                    hold the Northern Paoting-Tsangchow bund [<hi rend="italic">line?</hi>] and
                    where possible to repel any landing of enemy forces at coastal points.</p>
                <p>Sent to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
